		<h3>Breakfast</h3>
		<em>Hashbrowns</em>
		<img src="images/hashbrown.jpg" alt="Hashbrown">
		<h4>Ingredients</h4>
		<ul>

		    <li>2 lbs frozen hash browns</li>
		    <li>1/2 cup margarine or 1/2 cup butter, melted</li>
		    <li>1 (10 1/4 ounce) can cream of chicken soup</li>
		    <li>1 pint sour cream</li>
		    <li>1/2 cup onion, peeled and chopped</li>
		    <li>2 cups cheddar cheese, grated</li>
		    <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
		    <li>1/4 teaspoon pepper</li>

		</ul>
		<h4>Directions</h4>
		<ol>
		    <li>Preheat oven to 350°F and spray an 11 x 14 baking dish with cooking spray.</li>
		    <li>Mix the above ingredients together, place in prepared pan and bake for 45 minutes or until brown on top.</li>
		<ol>
